<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-524] Patches are not applied to the WAR distribution</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-524</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I noticed that the patches (e.g. httpcore-nio-4.0-patch-httpcore-193.jar) are bundled with the ZIP distribution, but not with the Web application. This could cause inconsistent behavior between a standalone deployment and a deployment into an application server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the servlet spec (SRV.9.5 in v2.4), &quot;The Web application class loader must load classes from the WEB-INF/classes directory first, and then from library JARs in the WEB-INF/lib directory.&quot; This gives a hint how to bundle these patches into the WAR so that the modified classes have priority.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12419260">SYNAPSE-524</key>
            <summary>Patches are not applied to the WAR distribution</summary>
